    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Contract Test Integration in CI Pipelines"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Contract tests run in two separate CI pipelines: one for each consumer service and one for the provider. The pipelines are intentionally decoupled \u2014 neither waits for the other to run first. Instead, the PACT broker acts as the coordination layer, holding verification results and answering can-i-deploy queries. This section covers the exact CI configuration for each side and how the broker ties them together."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Dual-pipeline CDC contract CI architecture",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Consumer CI Pipeline"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Each consumer service runs its pact tests in its own CI job. The job has three phases: run the consumer pact tests to generate the pact file, publish the pact to the broker tagged with the current git SHA, and check can-i-deploy before releasing."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# .github/workflows/consumer-ci.yml\n# Used by: chat-frontend, summary-service, embed-service\nname: Consumer CI\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [\"**\"]\n  pull_request: {}\n\njobs:\n  unit-and-pact:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n        with: {python-version: '3.12'}\n      - run: pip install -r requirements.txt pact-python pytest\n\n      - name: Run unit tests\n        run: pytest tests/unit/ -v\n\n      - name: Run consumer pact tests\n        run: pytest tests/pact/ -v\n        # This generates pacts/<consumer>-<provider>.json\n\n      - name: Publish pact to broker\n        if: github.event_name == 'push'\n        run: |\n          pact-broker publish pacts/ \\\n            --broker-base-url ${{ vars.PACT_BROKER_URL }} \\\n            --broker-token ${{ secrets.PACT_BROKER_TOKEN }} \\\n            --consumer-app-version ${{ github.sha }} \\\n            --branch ${{ github.ref_name }} \\\n            --tag ${{ github.ref_name }}\n\n  can-i-deploy:\n    needs: unit-and-pact\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/main'\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - run: pip install pact-python\n\n      - name: Wait for provider verification\n        # Polls the broker until provider verifies the pact or times out (10 min)\n        run: |\n          pact-broker can-i-deploy \\\n            --broker-base-url ${{ vars.PACT_BROKER_URL }} \\\n            --broker-token ${{ secrets.PACT_BROKER_TOKEN }} \\\n            --pacticipant ${{ env.CONSUMER_NAME }} \\\n            --version ${{ github.sha }} \\\n            --to-environment production \\\n            --retry-while-unknown 30 \\\n            --retry-interval 20\n        env:\n          CONSUMER_NAME: chat-frontend  # override per service\n\n  deploy:\n    needs: can-i-deploy\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - name: Deploy consumer\n        run: echo \"Deploy ${{ env.CONSUMER_NAME }} ${{ github.sha }} to production\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Provider CI Pipeline"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The provider CI fetches all consumer pacts from the broker, runs verification against the live provider, and records results back to the broker. The provider pipeline runs on every push and also when the broker fires a webhook after a consumer publishes a new pact."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# .github/workflows/provider-ci.yml\nname: Provider CI (claude-service)\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [\"**\"]\n  pull_request: {}\n  # Broker webhook fires this when any consumer publishes a new pact\n  repository_dispatch:\n    types: [pact-changed]\n\nenv:\n  PROVIDER_NAME: claude-service\n  PACT_PROVIDER_VERIFICATION: \"true\"\n\njobs:\n  unit-and-schema:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n        with: {python-version: '3.12'}\n      - run: pip install -r requirements.txt pact-python pytest pydantic\n\n      - name: Unit tests\n        run: pytest tests/unit/ -v\n\n      - name: Schema compatibility check\n        run: |\n          python scripts/export_tool_schemas.py --output /tmp/new-schemas/\n          for schema in contracts/tools/*.schema.json; do\n            tool=$(basename \"$schema\" .schema.json)\n            python scripts/check_schema_compat.py \"$schema\" \"/tmp/new-schemas/${tool}.schema.json\"\n          done\n\n  verify-pacts:\n    needs: unit-and-schema\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    env:\n      ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: ${{ secrets.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n        with: {python-version: '3.12'}\n      - run: pip install pact-python pytest uvicorn fastapi anthropic\n\n      - name: Verify all consumer pacts from broker\n        run: |\n          pytest tests/pact/verify_pacts.py -v \\\n            --provider-version=${{ github.sha }} \\\n            --provider-version-branch=${{ github.ref_name }} \\\n            --publish-verification-results\n\n        # verify_pacts.py reads PACT_BROKER_URL + PACT_BROKER_TOKEN from env\n        env:\n          PACT_BROKER_URL: ${{ vars.PACT_BROKER_URL }}\n          PACT_BROKER_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.PACT_BROKER_TOKEN }}\n\n  can-i-deploy:\n    needs: verify-pacts\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/main'\n    steps:\n      - run: pip install pact-python\n      - name: Can-I-Deploy provider to production\n        run: |\n          pact-broker can-i-deploy \\\n            --broker-base-url ${{ vars.PACT_BROKER_URL }} \\\n            --broker-token ${{ secrets.PACT_BROKER_TOKEN }} \\\n            --pacticipant ${{ env.PROVIDER_NAME }} \\\n            --version ${{ github.sha }} \\\n            --to-environment production\n\n  deploy:\n    needs: can-i-deploy\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - name: Deploy provider\n        run: echo \"Deploy claude-service ${{ github.sha }} to production\"\n\n      - name: Record deployment in broker\n        run: |\n          pact-broker record-deployment \\\n            --broker-base-url ${{ vars.PACT_BROKER_URL }} \\\n            --broker-token ${{ secrets.PACT_BROKER_TOKEN }} \\\n            --pacticipant ${{ env.PROVIDER_NAME }} \\\n            --version ${{ github.sha }} \\\n            --environment production\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Broker Webhook Configuration"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The broker webhook closes the feedback loop: when a consumer publishes a new pact, the broker immediately notifies the provider's CI so it can verify without waiting for the next scheduled build. Configure the webhook in the PACT broker UI or via its API."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "json"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "// POST to https://pact.mycompany.com/webhooks (PACT broker API)\n{\n  \"description\": \"Trigger provider CI when consumer pact changes\",\n  \"events\": [\n    {\"name\": \"contract_content_changed\"},\n    {\"name\": \"contract_published\"}\n  ],\n  \"request\": {\n    \"method\": \"POST\",\n    \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/myorg/claude-service/dispatches\",\n    \"headers\": {\n      \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n      \"Accept\": \"application/vnd.github.everest-preview+json\",\n      \"Authorization\": \"Bearer ${user.githubToken}\"\n    },\n    \"body\": {\n      \"event_type\": \"pact-changed\",\n      \"client_payload\": {\n        \"pact_url\": \"${pactbroker.pactUrl}\",\n        \"consumer\": \"${pactbroker.consumerName}\",\n        \"consumer_version\": \"${pactbroker.consumerVersionNumber}\"\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"provider\": {\"name\": \"claude-service\"},\n  \"consumer\": {}\n}\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Reading Webhook Payload in Provider CI"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# In verify-pacts job, detect if triggered by webhook and verify only the changed pact\n- name: Determine pacts to verify\n  run: |\n    if [ \"${{ github.event_name }}\" = \"repository_dispatch\" ]; then\n      echo \"PACT_URL=${{ github.event.client_payload.pact_url }}\" >> $GITHUB_ENV\n      echo \"Verifying single changed pact: $PACT_URL\"\n    else\n      echo \"PACT_URL=\" >> $GITHUB_ENV\n      echo \"Verifying all pacts from broker\"\n    fi\n\n- name: Verify pacts\n  run: |\n    if [ -n \"$PACT_URL\" ]; then\n      pytest tests/pact/verify_pacts.py -v -k \"not all\" \\\n        --pact-url=\"$PACT_URL\" \\\n        --publish-verification-results\n    else\n      pytest tests/pact/verify_pacts.py -v \\\n        --publish-verification-results\n    fi\n  env:\n    PROVIDER_VERSION: ${{ github.sha }}\n    PACT_BROKER_URL: ${{ vars.PACT_BROKER_URL }}\n    PACT_BROKER_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.PACT_BROKER_TOKEN }}\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Provider Verification Test with Broker Integration"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The provider verification test reads broker URL and credentials from environment variables, fetches all pacts, and publishes results back. This eliminates the need to check pacts into the provider repo."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# claude-service/tests/pact/verify_pacts.py\nimport os\nimport pytest\nimport uvicorn\nimport threading\nimport time\nfrom pact import Verifier\nfrom app import app\n\nPROVIDER_PORT = 9090\nPROVIDER_URL = f\"http://127.0.0.1:{PROVIDER_PORT}\"\nBROKER_URL = os.environ[\"PACT_BROKER_URL\"]\nBROKER_TOKEN = os.environ[\"PACT_BROKER_TOKEN\"]\nPROVIDER_VERSION = os.environ.get(\"PROVIDER_VERSION\", \"dev\")\nPROVIDER_BRANCH = os.environ.get(\"GITHUB_REF_NAME\", \"local\")\nPUBLISH_RESULTS = os.environ.get(\"PUBLISH_VERIFICATION_RESULTS\") == \"true\"\n\n@pytest.fixture(scope=\"module\", autouse=True)\ndef start_provider():\n    config = uvicorn.Config(app, host=\"127.0.0.1\", port=PROVIDER_PORT, log_level=\"error\")\n    server = uvicorn.Server(config)\n    thread = threading.Thread(target=server.run, daemon=True)\n    thread.start()\n    time.sleep(1)\n\ndef test_verify_all_consumer_pacts():\n    verifier = Verifier(\n        provider=\"claude-service\",\n        provider_base_url=PROVIDER_URL,\n    )\n    # Fetch pacts from broker, not from disk\n    success, _ = verifier.verify_with_broker(\n        broker_url=BROKER_URL,\n        broker_token=BROKER_TOKEN,\n        consumer_version_selectors=[\n            {\"mainBranch\": True},\n            {\"deployedOrReleased\": True},\n        ],\n        enable_pending=True,          # new pacts don't block CI until first verification\n        include_wip_pacts_since=\"2025-01-01\",\n        provider_version=PROVIDER_VERSION,\n        provider_version_branch=PROVIDER_BRANCH,\n        publish_verification_results=PUBLISH_RESULTS,\n        provider_states_setup_url=f\"{PROVIDER_URL}/_pact/provider-states\",\n    )\n    assert success == 0, \"One or more consumer pacts failed provider verification\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pending Pacts and WIP Pacts"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Two broker features prevent a consumer's new pact from immediately blocking the provider's build before the provider team has had a chance to implement the changes."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
