          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Contract test CI integration follows the dual-pipeline pattern: consumers publish pacts on every push, providers verify pacts whenever triggered by a push or broker webhook, and the PACT broker's can-i-deploy API enforces the gate before every deployment to every environment. Enable pending pacts so new consumer pacts don't immediately break provider CI. Record every deployment so can-i-deploy can answer environment-level questions accurately. Engineers can run verification locally against checked-in pact files without accessing the broker at all."
          }
        ]
